definition: two quite different things/another kettle of fish
two/both/some/a few/tael, unit of weight equal to 50 grams (modern) or 1⁄16 of a catty 斤[jin1] (old)
weight/number/code/to pile/to stack/classifier for length or distance (yard), happenings etc

sentences.english: It was not an explosion in which debris flung out into a pre-existing space.
sentences.chinese: 这和爆炸后撒了一地的残瓦碎片完全是两码事。
当然，老鼠跟人毕竟是两码事。

sentences.english: The past and the future is always different.
sentences.chinese: 过去和未来从来都是两码事。

sentences.english: But the exact number itself is altogether different.
sentences.chinese: 但是性伴侣的确切数量本身完全是两码事。

sentences.english: Initial selection and the interview itself are two different things.
sentences.chinese: 初步的筛选与面试本身是两码事。

sentences.english: “That’s not the same thing, ” I said.
Advising people and writing are fundamentally different types of work.
sentences.chinese: 咨询和写作完全是两码事。

sentences.english: But having her hair fall out while undergoing cancer treatment was a different matter.
sentences.chinese: 但是当时剪头发和因为癌症治疗而剪头发是两码事。

sentences.english: What the PRC claims and what it honestly has claim to are two vastly different things.
sentences.chinese: 中国所声称的和真实应该声称的根本就是两码事好嘛。

sentences.english: Caution is one thing and waving is another.
sentences.chinese: 谨慎小心和举棋不定是两码事。

sentences.english: What I mean is that the Premier League and the Champions League are two different things.
sentences.chinese: 我的意思是，英超和冠军联赛完全是两码事。

definition: two quite different things/two unrelated matters
see 沒關係|没关系[mei2 guan1 xi5]
to confuse one thing with another (idiom); to muddle
unrelated/having nothing to do (with sth else)
to equate/to consider (two things) to be equivalent
at a loss/unable to do anything about it/to have no choice
